**Problem Statement**

Decommission DTSKs assigned to the backup team require manual validation before the task can be progressed.
For each DTSK, the team needs to identify the associated CI, check whether the CI exists in Cohesity, confirm latest backup evidence, capture the protection group, and verify whether the task is assigned and still within the 2-day SLA.

This manual process is time-consuming, inconsistent, and can lead to missed unassigned tasks, overdue DTSKs, or incomplete backup evidence. There is also added complexity when the same CI appears in multiple Cohesity clusters due to replication.

**Approach**

Use the existing DTSK search output from ServiceNow as the input to a Dynatrace workflow.
The workflow will pass the CI details to a JavaScript task that uses Cohesity Helios GET APIs to search protected objects across all clusters.

The script will validate the CI backup evidence, identify the selected cluster, matched clusters, protection group, latest backup date, assignment status, and SLA status. It will also handle cases where no DTSKs are returned.

**Solution**

Automate the validation through a scheduled Dynatrace workflow running every 6 hours.
The workflow will generate an email report with summary counts, DTSK details, assignment status, SLA status, backup status, latest backup date, protection group, and matched cluster details.

This will reduce manual checks, provide consistent evidence, improve SLA visibility, and help the team quickly identify unassigned, overdue, unprotected, or replicated CI scenarios.
